centos 7.3 nginx with php via php-fpm, the env in php is cleaned by php-fpm

u can use putenv to set evn["PATH"] in php code, examples

    putenv("PATH=/sbin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin"); 
    var_dump(shell_exec('unoconv -vvvv -f pdf -o 123.pdf 123.doc));

or u can set env use one line shell cmd

    var_dump(shell_exec('PATH=/sbin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin'.' unoconv -vvvv -f pdf -o 123.pdf 123.doc));

or u can change php-fpm.d/www.conf to pass the env to php, add this line

    clean_env = no

and the restart php-fpm

    systemctl restart php-fpm.service

The "number" parser I shared above was really just an example... it doesn't handle empty strings, remove commas spaces and other non-digit characters, nor does it return the string if the result is not a numeric value. The built-in "digit" parser should do all that automatically.

Anyway, it would help if you could share some example values from the column causing problems.

Lastly, the `change` callback in the ajax success function should be moved outside of that function and use delegated binding instead of binding directly to the checkbox. Something like this:

```js
$("table tbody").on("change", ":checkbox", function(){
    $(this).closest('tr').toggleClass('selected', this.checked);
    addItems($(this).val(), this.checked);
});

$.ajax(
{
    // ...
    success: function(feedback)
    {
        // remove $('tbody :checkbox').change code from here
    }
});
```

