@ibobak,
I figured it out the issue early this morning, also on a BDA. The issue we run into the error of "cloud size under xx" is because I try to run sparkling-shell on edge node. Once I installed the package on one of BDA node. It worked and I can see H2O Flow UI. From the sparking-shell, it shows that the UI address is the BDA node's InfinitBand private IP address. As edge node can not communicate to the BDA's private IB network, no wonder it is timed out and never get the response back. Hope it helps.

