@msarahan If it helps, I have a routine [here](https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit/pull/211#issuecomment-186466605) that tries to find your codes indentation level, that you can
feed into `ruamel.yaml.dump(......., indent=your_indent)`. That will still mangle inconsistent indenting because no information is kept on a individual basis, and also key aligns the dashes of a list.

You can of course also hard-code 4 (or any other positive value) indents if that is what always should be used instead of the default of 2 that ruamel.yaml uses.

