@rmatev We don't mix LHCbDirac (or DIRAC) with Ganga due to a few different reasons. The first is that both ourselves and DIRAC used to have conflicting external dependencies (this may or may not be the case at the moment I've not checked in a while myself). But in addition to this there are a large number of calls to DIRAC made by Ganga which can fail due to different reasons and when they do we prefer to have some wrapper to isolate Ganga from this a bit more to prevent the rest of Ganga having problems.

